Re: resource hog

Bitcointalk

2010-07-14 16:29:39 UTC - [11]Original Post

   In Windows, you select the process in the task manager, right click,
   Set Priority.  Set it to BelowNormal or Low.  That shouldnʼt make a
   difference though.
   If you turn off Generate Coins, does the CPU usage go flat?  That would
   confirm that all the CPU time itʼs taking is generate, which is idle
   priority already.
   It could be itʼs slow just because you have too many things running at
   once and youʼre out of memory.  When you switch from one thing to
   another, it has to page it in from disk.
